      "description": "Restructure CMS Team Member Schema with Localized Biography Fields\n\nRefactor the team member data structure in the CMS to include localized biography fields directly in the team member schema, eliminating the need for separate translation key-value pairs.\n\nRequirements:\n- Update team member schema to include dedicated fields: bio_en, bio_pl, and any other required language variants\n- Remove biography-related translation keys from the separate translation schema\n- Migrate existing biography data from translation key-value structure to the new direct fields\n- Update team building/rendering logic to read biography from the new schema structure\n- Ensure all language configurations are properly mapped (config_en, config_pl, etc.)\n- Verify that the team display correctly shows localized biographies based on active language\n- Update any CMS documentation or admin interfaces to reflect the new schema structure\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Handle team members with missing biography translations gracefully\n- Ensure backward compatibility during migration if needed\n- Validate that no biography content is lost during restructuring",
